(162, 'Site Update', 'About the Audifan Happy Box', '', 'The <a href="/community/happybox/">Audifan Happy Box</a> is Audifan''s new way of giving you the chance to win Bana Cash!\r\n\r\nYou can spin the Happy Box every 8 hours.  Those who have VIP Status can spin every 4 hours.\r\n\r\nEach time you spin the Happy Box, you have a chance of winning any of the following prizes:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>-10% Cooldown Timer Item (Medium Chance)\r\nReduces time between Happy Box spins by 10%.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>-25% Cooldown Timer Item (Medium Chance)\r\nReduces time between Happy Box spins by 25%.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>-50% Cooldown Timer Item (Low Chance)\r\nReduces time between Happy Box spins by 50%.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>VIP Drawing Entry (Very Low Chance)\r\nGives you an additional entry in the VIP Drawing.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>INSTANT $5 Bana Cash Win (Extremely Low Chance)\r\nYou instantly win $5 Bana Cash!  You must submit your Audition In-Game Name to us within ONE WEEK of winning, or it will disappear.  The cash will be given in the exact manner, and with the same stipulations, as our <a href="/community/vipdrawing/">VIP Drawing</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nAdditional Prize Info:\r\n- Cooldown timer items WILL STACK with the VIP Status effect, but the items WILL NOT STACK with each other. If you win a cooldown timer item, only the "best" one that you have will be retained.  If the one you win is better than one that you already have, it will be replaced for the full duration.  If the one you win is worse, the duration for the one you already have will be extended by 4 hours.\r\n- You must already have at least 1 entry in the VIP Drawing to be able to win the additional VIP Drawing entry prize.\r\n\r\nPlease send us your feedback!  We would greatly appreciate it.\r\n\r\nThank you for using Audifan!\r\n\r\n<u>Archived Changes in Beta</u>\r\n[9/29]\r\n- Significantly lowered the chance of receiving a VIP Drawing entry.\r\n\r\n[9/30]\r\n- Winning a cooldown item that is "worse" than one that you already have will now only extend the time left by 8 hours, instead of completely renewing the time left.\r\n- Added tooltips to the items won in "Recent Winners."\r\n\r\n[10/2]\r\n- Reduced number of recent winners to 15.\r\n- There is now a chance that you will receive a bonus spin if you don''t win anything.\r\n\r\n[10/4]\r\n- Winning a lesser cooldown item now extends the time by 4 hours (down from 8 hours).\r\n- Fixed a display issue where winning an improved cooldown item made the Happy Box show a stacked effect, with the item you won and item you already had both affecting the time between spins.\r\n- Note that all items won in beta have now been removed and all spin cooldowns have been reset.  Thanks for helping us test!', 1380922893),
(163, 'Site News', 'September VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congrats to <a href="/community/profile/2124/">Super</a> for winning the September VIP Drawing!\r\n<iframe width="500" height="281" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/6bsi4L1z-gs" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 1380926490),
(164, 'Audition Update', 'October 16, 2013 Patch', '', '- 58 New Fashion Mall Items\r\n\r\nMore info: <a href="/patch/20131016">October 16, 2013 Patch Info</a>\r\n\r\n<a href="/patch/manualpatches/">Manual patches</a>', 1381958865),
(165, 'Audition Update', 'October 30, 2013 Patch', '', '- Account PINs\r\n- 2 New Songs\r\n- 2 New Night Dance Songs\r\n- 2 New Beat Up Songs\r\n- 2 New One Two Party Songs\r\n- 161 New Fashion Mall Items\r\n- 16 New Couple Shop Items\r\n\r\nMore info: <a href="/patch/20131030/">October 30, 2013 Patch Info</a>\r\n\r\n<a href="/patch/manualpatches/">Manual patches</a>\r\n', 1383181810),
(166, 'Site News', 'October VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congrats to <a href="/community/profile/1640/">pugs</a> for winning the October VIP Drawing!<br />\r\n<iframe width="500" height="281" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/CdnUGzN8qvM" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 1383360593),
(167, 'Audition Update', 'November 6, 2013 Patch', '', '- 2 New Songs\r\n- 2 New Night Dance Songs\r\n- 2 New Beat Up Songs\r\n- 2 New One Two Party Songs\r\n\r\nMore info: <a href="/patch/20131106/">November 6, 2013 Patch Info</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href="/patch/manualpatches/">Manual patches</a>', 1383813505),
(168, 'Audition Update', 'November 13, 2013 Patch', '', '- 106 New Fashion Mall Items\r\n\r\nMore info: <a href="/patch/20131113/">November 13, 2013 Patch Info</a>\r\n\r\n<a href="/patch/manualpatches/">Manual patches</a>', 1384370999),
(169, 'Site News', 'Peach Emote Removal', '', 'It has come to our attention that the peach emotes from Audition that we have on the site were wrongfully distributed after they were taken from someone who took the time to create them.\r\n\r\nBeing content creators ourselves, it''s extremely disappointing when anyone takes your work and portrays it as being their own.  Therefore, we are going to remove the peach emotes as soon as possible.  Any existing emotes in comments or "About Me" sections of profiles will be replaced with the text of the emote.\r\n\r\nWe will work to add the peach emotes back as soon as possible.\r\n\r\nThanks!', 1385416850),
(170, 'Audition Update', 'November 27, 2013 Patch', '', '- Couple Garden Attendance\r\n- Black Friday Deals\r\n- Event Server\r\n- 475 new items now have the indefinite purchase option\r\n- 3 New Songs\r\n- 3 New Night Dance Songs\r\n- 3 New Beat Up Songs\r\n- 3 New One Two Party Songs\r\n- 106 New Fashion Mall Items\r\n- 5 New Couple Garden Market Items\r\n- X-Trap Update\r\n\r\nMore info: <a href="/patch/20131127/">November 27, 2013 Patch Info</a>\r\n\r\n<a href="/patch/manualpatches/">Manual patches</a>\r\n', 1385554920),
(171, 'Site News', 'November VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congrats to <a href="/community/profile/2385/">Pipay</a> for winning the November VIP Drawing!<br />\r\n<iframe width="500" height="281" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/vjSbd-bOlLw" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 1385746055),
(172, 'Site Update', 'New Rings Added to Character Info', '', 'Most of the non-animated rings from the Couple Shop can now be added to your character info!\r\n\r\nYou can add them to your characters on the <a href="/community/profile/edit/character/">Edit Characters</a> page.\r\n\r\nYou can also add them to sigs created by the <a href="/community/siggenerator/">Signature Generator</a>.', 1386640140),
(173, 'Audition Update', 'December 11, 2013 Patch', '', '107 new Fashion Mall items added.\r\n\r\n<a href="/patch/20131211/">More info</a>. <a href="/patch/manualpatches/">Manual Patches</a>.', 1386790298),
(174, 'Audition Update', 'December 18, 2013 Patch', '', '- Audition Gift Box\r\n- Audition Town Christmas Theme\r\n- Event Server\r\n- New Song\r\n- New Night Dance Song\r\n- New Beat Up Song\r\n- New One Two Party Song\r\n- New Guitar Song\r\n- 113 New Fashion Mall Items\r\n- X-Trap Update\r\n\r\n<a href="/patch/20131218/">More info</a>. <a href="/patch/manualpatches/">Manual Patches</a>. ', 1387411038),
(175, 'Site Update', 'Happy Box Update', '', 'A few things have been changed with the Happy Box.\r\n\r\n- Added spinning sound.\r\n- Slightly lowered chance to receive a VIP Drawing entry.\r\n\r\nA bug fix was attempted, but it didn''t work! :(\r\nAnother bug fix and another update will be applied soon.', 1387876522),
(176, 'Audition Update', 'December 30, 2013 Patch', '', '- Year End Sale\r\n- 320 new items now have the indefinite purchase option.\r\n- XTrap update\r\n\r\n<a href="/patch/20131230/">More info</a>. <a href="/patch/manualpatches/">Manual Patches</a>.', 1388404945),
(177, 'Site News', 'December VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Sorry we were a day late with the drawing.\r\n\r\nCongrats to <a href="/community/profile/45/">Bri</a> for winning the December VIP Drawing!<br /><br />\r\n<iframe width="500" height="281" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/ox6o794HcDE" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 1388862946),
(178, 'Site Update', 'Song Lengths Added to Song List', '', 'Song lengths have been added to the song list!\r\n\r\nThey are approximate, but if you find one that''s severely incorrect, please let us know!\r\n\r\nGuitar song lengths and Ballroom song lengths will be added in the future.\r\n\r\n<a href="/music/list/">http://www.audifan.net/music/list/</a>', 1389660392),
(179, 'Misc', 'European Audition Closing', '', 'We were so incredibly saddened to hear that European Audition is closing.  \r\n\r\nTo anyone from EAU who is considering moving to Redbana Audition, we want to help you any way we can.  Just <a href="/contactus/" target="_blank">contact us through the site</a>, <a href="http://forums.redbana.com/private.php?do=newpm&u=12929" target="_blank">send a message on Redbana Forums to tr848</a>, or <a href="/community/profile/1/comments/" target="_blank">add a comment to tr848''s profile</a> if you need anything while transitioning to our server.\r\n\r\nWe''re glad that you''re here, but we''re so sorry for the circumstances.', 1391200966),
(180, 'Site News', 'Final VIP Drawing & Removal of HB Cash Prize', '', 'We will be discontinuing VIP Drawings after the February 2014 drawing.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, we have removed the Bana Cash prize from the Happy Box.\r\n\r\nSince we started giving away Bana Cash, we have given away over $100 in prizes to our wonderfully dedicated Audifans.\r\n\r\nWe unfortunately are no longer going to be able to give out cash.\r\n\r\nThank you all so much for your support of these features over the past year and a half.', 1392744257),
(181, 'Audition Update', 'May 28, 2014 Patch Info', '/patch/20140528/', '', 1401390448),
(182, 'Site News', 'Nickname Requirement Change', '', 'Hi everyone.\r\n\r\nWe have changed our nickname format requirements.  Nicknames may now only contain letters, numbers, underscores ( _ ), dashes ( - ), and tildes ( ~ ).  This requirement is the same as Audition''s IGN requirement.\r\n\r\nWe made this change in order to increase the security of our site.  A few accounts with malicious names have been made, and restricting the requirements will protect against future threats.\r\n\r\nWe will also be changing existing nicknames in order to fit the new requirement.  Therefore, <span style="font-weight:bold;">if your nickname does not meet the above requirements by Sunday, June 22, 2014, <span style="text-decoration:underline;">your name will be changed to a generic one</span></span>.  This currently affects 197 people.\r\n\r\nAll name change timers have been reset, and they will be reset again on June 22.  Also, we have changed the timer so that you can change your name once every 15 days (down from 90).\r\n\r\nWe apologize for the inconvenience.', 1402386491),
(183, 'Site Update', 'Profile/Sig Generator Update', '', 'The last E2 story medal and 3 new Couple Shop rings (Cream Pudding, Forever Heart, and Soft-Sheep Head) have been added to profiles and the Signature Generator.', 1402428955),
(184, 'Audition Update', '6/14 Site Updates', '', '- Added new, smaller MyAudifan that fits on one side of the page.\r\n- Rearranged some stuff on the homepage to accommodate for the new MyAudifan.\r\n- Added rounded edges and shadows to menu and some other navigational content.\r\n- Added new logo.\r\n- Increased maximum friends to 300 (up from 200).\r\n- Various sever upgrades.', 1402798484),
(185, 'Site News', 'Garden Notifications Fixed', '', 'The Couple Garden Timer desktop notifications have been fixed to work with the newer versions of Google Chrome.  If desktop notifications no longer work for you, be sure to update your browser to the latest version.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, desktop notifications are now supported for Firefox.  However, Firefox forces notifications to disappear after about 4 seconds after they appear if you do not mouse over them.  For this reason, we still recommend Chrome if you would like to use desktop notifications.\r\n\r\nThank you to Audifan members Joseph and Leonardo Buares for sending us further information on fixing the issues.', 1404262395),
(186, 'Site News', '"My Audifan" Fixed', '', 'We fixed a major error affecting some members where My Audifan on the homepage halted execution prematurely, resulting in corrupted data being sent from the server.\r\n\r\nWe apologize for any confusion caused by this.', 1404263461),
(187, 'Site News', 'Manual Patch Changes', '', 'Since there has been some confusion, starting with the newest manual patch (10234 to 10236), there have been some changes.\r\n\r\nThe manual patches will now extract to /Program Files/Redbana/Audition on ALL operating systems instead of extracting to /Program Files (x86)/Redbana/Audition on 64-bit operating systems.  The installer explicitly installs Audition to the "Program Files" folder, and it was causing many people to install manual patches to the wrong location.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, in order to further confirm that you are installing to the correct folder, messages will now appear asking you to confirm that you would like to replace existing files.  Just select "Yes to All" on the message.  If no message appears, you are likely installing to the wrong folder.', 1404320714),
(188, 'Site Update', 'New EXP Calculator', '/guides/exp/', '', 1404620351),
(189, 'Site News', 'Nicknames (Finally) Changed', '', 'In a previous post, we announced that our nickname requirements have changed.  Nicknames that no longer met the requirements were changed today to a generic name.  If you have a generic name, you can change it on the <a href="/account/myaccount/">My Account page</a>.', 1406213284),
(190, 'Site Update', 'New Patch Listings By Year', '', 'You can now see all patches from an entire year on the patch archive.\r\n\r\nClick the year you want to browse from the new links on the menu under "Patches".', 1407445268),
(191, 'Site Update', 'Audifan Quests', '', 'Audifan Quests are here!\r\n<a href="/quests/">http://audifan.net/quests/</a>\r\n\r\nEach Sunday night, four quests are chosen with difficulties from Easy to Insane. You''ll have one week to complete the quests and submit screenshots for each.  Complete quests to challenge your skills and to earn Quest Points.  Climb the overall and mode rankings to show your strengths.  Earn medals to show off your skills.  Can you knock out all four quests and become an ACE?\r\n\r\nFull details of this big update are below, plus you can check out the <a href="/quests/">quests page</a> for more details.\r\n\r\nDetailed update notes:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>How Do Quests Work?<ul>\r\n		<li>Four quests are randomly chosen at 11:59 pm on Sunday nights.</li>\r\n		<li>Screenshots must be submitted by 11:50pm the following Sunday.  From 11:50 to 11:59, screenshots cannot be submitted.</li>\r\n		<li>Quests range from getting a high score or getting no misses to simply wearing an item while playing, and everything in between.  They also span many modes including expert tournament modes, Beat Up, Beat Rush, One Two Party, Rhythmholic, and more.</li>\r\n		<li>A quest may not be chosen again for five weeks after it is picked.</li>\r\n		<li>Have an idea for a quest?  We''d love to hear it!  Use our Contact Us form or message tr848 on Redbana Forums.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n	<li>Submitting a Screenshot<ul>\r\n		<li>Click Submit a Screenshot to upload a screenshot for a quest.</li>\r\n		<li>Screenshots will be uploaded to ImageShack in a private album after they are verified.  If ImageShack is not available, they will stay with Audifan.</li>\r\n		<li>ALL screenshots MUST follow the submission requirements as listed on the <a href="/quests/submit/">Submit a Screenshot</a> page.  The requirements are:<ul>\r\n			<li>You must submit a screenshot of the final scoreboard at the end of the game.</li>\r\n			<li>You must use the /time command to display the time in chat in the screenshot. The screenshot must be taken within the current submission period.</li>\r\n			<li>The screenshot you submit must be a screenshot taken by pressing the Print Screen (PrtScn) button and saved to your Audition "screenshot" folder. It may not be taken with any other program such as Fraps or saved by pasting into Photoshop, Paint, etc.</li>\r\n			<li>The screenshot cannot be edited in any way. It must be the same exact file that was saved to your screenshot folder. You will be permanently banned from Audifan if you try to cheat.</li>\r\n		</ul></li>\r\n		<li>A grader will check your screenshot as soon as possible after you submit it.</li>\r\n		<li>You can check the status, view the screenshot, or delete a submission on the <a href="/quests/submissions/">Submission Details page</a>.</li>\r\n		<li>If one of your screenshots is rejected by a grader while there is still time left to submit, you can submit again.  However, there is NO guarantee that the screenshot will be graded before time is up, so please double check your submissions!</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n	<li>Scoring and Medals<ul>\r\n		<li>Quests are worth a certain amount of Quest Points (QP). Easy quests are worth 2 points, Medium are worth 4, Hard are worth 8, and Insane are worth 12.</li>\r\n		<li>You can also earn a medal depending on which quests you complete:<ul>\r\n			<li>Easy quest only: Thumbs Up <img src="/img/quest/badge1.png" /></li>\r\n			<li>Easy + Medium quests: Bronze <img src="/img/quest/badge2.png" /></li>\r\n			<li>Easy + Medium + Hard: Silver <img src="/img/quest/badge3.gif" /></li>\r\n			<li>All (ACE): Gold <img src="/img/quest/badge4.gif" /></li>\r\n		</ul></li>\r\n		<li>Your medal will appear on your profile, in comments on MyAudifan on the homepage, and next to your name on the rankings.</li>\r\n		<li>If you are an ACE (completed all quests), your name will appear on the Quests page.</li>\r\n		<li>Your QP and medal will be updated after all screenshots from all participants have been graded for the week.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n	<li>Rankings<ul>\r\n		<li>Ties are broken in favor of whomever was first to start doing quests.  In other words, the person who has the earliest timestamp on their first submission ever.</li>\r\n		<li>Each ranking board has a description of how points are determined.</li>\r\n		<li>Ranking are usually updated immediately after points are updated.  However, you can see when rankings were last updated on any Ranking page.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n	<li>Additional Updates<ul>\r\n		<li>If you are logged in, you can see the status of your submissions, your total QP, and your overall ranking at the top of any page, attached to the top of the menu.</li>\r\n		<li>You can add a new Quest Stats module to your profile.  Go to the <a href="/community/profile/edit/">Edit Profile Layout</a> page to do so.</li>\r\n		<li>A new category to the menu has been added for Site Events like quests and VIP info.  You can click the <a href="/siteevents/">Site Events</a> link on the menu to see a description of all of Audifan''s site events.</li>\r\n		<li>Fixed the scroller speed to be proportional to the entire scroller''s width instead of the text''s width.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\nAlso, please keep in mind that quests are in BETA.  This means preliminary testing is finished (thank you to everyone who helped test!!!), but bugs may still exist and features may still be added or removed.  Please report anything out of the ordinary via our Contact Us form, or message tr848 on Redbana Forums.', 1411436028),
(192, 'Site Update', 'My Stuff', '', '<a href="/account/stuff/">My Stuff</a> is a new page for all badges and items that you receive from site events.\r\n\r\nTo see your stuff, click the link under My Profile at the top of any page.\r\n<img src="http://i.imgur.com/mzOTVo6.png" />\r\n\r\nYou can see how long you have left on each badge and change a badge''s visibility by turning it on or off.', 1411436028),
(193, 'Site Update', 'The VIP Drawing is back!', '', 'The VIP Drawing is back with new prizes!\r\nCheck out the VIP Drawing page for all of the details on how to earn entries and what you can win!\r\n\r\n<a href="/community/vipdrawing/">http://www.audifan.net/community/vipdrawing/</a>', 1412322392),
(194, 'Site Update', 'The Happy Box is back!', '', 'The Happy Box is back with new prizes and new cooldown bonuses!\r\n<a href="/community/happybox/">www.audifan.net/community/happybox/</a>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Prizes<ul>\r\n	<li>Badges<ul>\r\n		<li>Badges appear with your name on your profile and on MyAudifan.</li>\r\n		<li>Badges last 30 days and you may have a maximum of 2 badges at any time.</li>\r\n		<li>Upon winning a Badge Voucher, you can redeem it on the My Stuff page.</li>\r\n		<li>There are 14 badges to choose from including tournament medals, mission icons, and other miscellaneous Audition flair.</li>\r\n		<li><img src="/img/icons/badges/16.png" /><img src="/img/icons/badges/17.png" /><img src="/img/icons/badges/18.png" /><img src="/img/icons/badges/19.png" /><img src="/img/icons/badges/20.png" /><img src="/img/icons/badges/21.png" /><img src="/img/icons/badges/22.png" /><br /><img src="/img/icons/badges/23.png" /><img src="/img/icons/badges/24.png" /><img src="/img/icons/badges/25.png" /><img src="/img/icons/badges/26.png" /><img src="/img/icons/badges/27.png" /><img src="/img/icons/badges/28.png" /><img src="/img/icons/badges/29.png" /></li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n	<li>Additional VIP Drawing Entries<ul>\r\n		<li>Adds an additional entry in the <a href="/community/vipdrawing/">VIP Drawing</a>.</li>\r\n		<li>Can only be won if you already won an entry by earning VIP Status.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n	<li>Cooldown Reduction Items (see below)</li>\r\n	<li>If you do not win anything, there is a <s>20%</s> 33% chance that you will receive a bonus spin.</li>\r\n</ul></li>\r\n\r\n<li>Cooldown Bonuses<ul>\r\n	<li>You can spin the Happy Box once every 8 hours.  However, you can reduce this cooldown time in many ways.</li>\r\n	<li>1. Win a cooldown item from the Happy Box itself!  -10%, -25%, and -40% cooldown reduction items can be won.  These items last 5 days.  The items do not stack with each other and will be replaced if you win a better one (e.g. a -40% item is better than a -25% item).  If you win the same item, the time will be extended 5 more days.</li>\r\n	<li>2. Earn VIP Status.  If you have a VIP badge, your cooldown will be reduced by 40%.</li>\r\n	<li>3. Earn Quest Points.  You will receive a cooldown reduction of approximately 0.081% per Quest Point, up to a maximum of 50.00% reduction.</li>\r\n	<li>4. Earn a Quest medal.<ul>\r\n		<li>Thumbs Up (Easy quest completed) - Reduces cooldown by 7 1/2 minutes.</li>\r\n		<li>Bronze Medal (Easy + Medium quests) - Reduces cooldown by 15 minutes.</li>\r\n		<li>Silver Medal (Easy, Medium, & Hard quests) - Reduces cooldown by 22 1/2 minutes.</li>\r\n		<li>Gold Medal (All quests completed) - Reduces cooldown by 30 minutes.</li>\r\n		<li>Reduction from quest medals are applied last and do not stack with other bonuses.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n	<li>All of your active cooldown bonuses are listed on the Happy Box page.</li>\r\n</ul></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nAs always, we welcome your feedback!  Please contact us through the website or message tr848 on Redbana Forums.\r\n\r\nThank you for your continued support of Audifan!', 1415064512),
(195, 'Site News', 'Contact Us Form Fixed', '', 'There was an issue with the Contact Us form and messages were not sent to us if you did not enter an email address, even though a confirmation message appeared.  The issue has been fixed, and emails are no longer required.\r\n\r\nIf you sent us a message without an email recently, you will have to resend it.  Sorry for the confusion.', 1414290338),
(196, 'Site Event', 'October VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congrats to <a href="/community/profile/330/">LunarViolet</a> (ID: 330) for winning!\r\n\r\n<img src="http://i.imgur.com/LU4Zga9.png" />', 1414752514),
(197, 'Site Update', 'Guitar Quests', '', 'Guitar Mode objectives have been added to the pool of quests and a Guitar Mode ranking board has been added.\r\n\r\nPlease note that all Guitar Mode quests require that you are the only player in the room.  This is to guarantee that graders can see the /time command in the screenshot.', 1418103678),
(198, 'Hidden', 'Improved Profile Editing', '', '', 1415124493),
(199, 'Hidden', 'New Message Boards', '', '', 1415124508),
(200, 'Site Update', 'Minor Happy Box Changes', '', 'Some drop rates have been tweaked for the Happy Box.\r\n\r\nThe chance of winning a badge and a 10% cooldown item has been lowered, and the chance of winning a VIP drawing entry has been raised.\r\n\r\nAlso, the chance of getting a bonus spin when you don''t win anything has been increased to 33% (up from 20%).', 1415742544),
(201, 'Site Event', 'November VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congrats to <a href="/community/profile/3276">Nyuli</a> (# 3276) for winning!\r\n\r\n<img src="http://i.imgur.com/nAX5mb9.png" />', 1417822144);
INSERT INTO `News` (`id`, `type`, `title`, `link`, `description`, `time`) VALUES
(202, 'Audition News', 'Audition has been greenlit!', '', 'Audition has been greenlit by the Steam community!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=297043839" target="_blank">http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=297043839</a>\r\n\r\nThank you to everyone who voted for Audition!', 1418098484),
(203, 'Site News', 'Periodic Server Maintenance', '', 'Today (December 10) through Friday, December 12, Audifan''s hosting provider will be installing updates to our server at arbitrary times throughout the day.  \r\n\r\nAt any time during this period, Audifan may be periodically inaccessible for up to an hour at a time.\r\n\r\nEverything should be done by Friday at 2 am EST.\r\n\r\nSorry in advance for any inconvenience caused.', 1418212742),
(204, 'Site Event', 'Grab a Badge!', '', 'Until the end of the year, a badge will be given if you do not win any other prize from the Happy Box.  If you already have two badges or badge vouchers, it does not apply.\r\n\r\nBe sure to grab a badge (or two) before 2014 is over!', 1419186505),
(205, 'Site News', 'Possible Quest Issues Tomorrow', '', 'Similar to <a href="/news/view/115/" target="_blank">what happened once</a> with the VIP Drawing, I once again forgot about the week when the year changes when I was making quests.\r\n\r\nI just implemented a fix to prevent problems tomorrow, but please be on the lookout for any further issues that I missed such as submissions disappearing or any changes that do not look right.\r\nYou can report them by <a href="/community/profile/1/comments/" target="_blank">leaving me a comment</a>.\r\n\r\nThanks and Happy New Year!', 1420058221),
(206, 'Site Event', 'December VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congrats to Carma for winning the December VIP Drawing!\r\n<img src="http://i.imgur.com/dWkAwzm.png" />', 1420260585),
(207, 'Site Update', 'New Quest Archive', '', 'A new <a href="/quests/archive/" target="_blank">quest archive</a> has been added to the site.\n\nAlso, archived submissions have been deleted from the database.', 1421712395),
(208, 'Site Event', 'January VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congrats to Blur for winning the January VIP Drawing!\n<img src="http://i.imgur.com/dCa3B8g.png" />\n\nThe drawing should have taken place on January 30, but actually took place on February 2.\nAll entries earned after January 30 were removed for the January drawing and then re-added after the drawing.\nSorry for the delay.', 1422855334),
(209, 'Site News', 'Profile Picture Rollback', '', 'We had to restore a backup of profile pictures from January 30, 2015.\r\n\r\nIf you changed your picture since then, you will have to change it again.\r\n\r\nSorry about the issue.', 1424835313),
(210, 'Site Event', 'February VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congrats to Maki for winning the February VIP Drawing!\r\n<img src="http://i.imgur.com/ENx166L.png" />', 1425105055),
(211, 'Hidden', 'Mandrake Timer Guide', '', 'The timers for a mandrake are in a table because many actions take the same amount of time to appear, but they are in different stages of mandrake growth.\r\n\r\nHere''s how to use the new mandrake timers on the Couple Garden Timer:\r\n\r\n1. Find the row for the current stage that your mandrake is on.\r\n2. Find the action that you just completed on that stage.\r\n3. Start the timer directly below the action.\r\n\r\nHere''s an example:\r\n<img src="/img/couplegarden/mandrakevisguide.png" />', 1425659107),
(212, 'Site News', 'Mandrake Timer Update', '', 'The mandrake timer interface is essentially finished, but the timer is still not accurate enough to release.\r\n\r\nWe''re having some trouble pinpointing the exact times when a mandrake will need something.\r\n\r\nA Facebook post mentioned that we would have the mandrake timer released sometime this week.  However, given that it is still not yet 100% accurate, we will not be able to.\r\n\r\nWe''ll continue to work on it and hopefully have it out for you soon!\r\n\r\nSorry for the delay!', 1426582878),
(213, 'Site Update', 'Secret Episode added to Story Guide', '/guides/story/', '', 1426582911),
(214, 'Site Event', 'March VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congratulations to Leebyn for winning the March VIP Drawing!\r\n<img src="http://i.imgur.com/D4EINvS.png" />', 1428144603),
(215, 'Hidden', 'Quest Grader Needed!', '', 'We''re looking for someone to help grade quest screenshot submissions!\r\n\r\nIf you''re interested, please PM tr848 on Redbana Forums:\r\n<a href="http://forums.redbana.com/privatemessage/new/12929" target="_blank">http://forums.redbana.com/privatemessage/new/12929</a>\r\n\r\nPlease include your Audifan nickname in your message.', 1428145260),
(216, 'Site Event', 'April VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congrats to HunnyPot for winning the April VIP Drawing!\r\n<img src="http://i.imgur.com/bDJWrh0.png" />', 1430550046),
(217, 'Site Update', 'VIP Drawing Automation', '', 'The VIP Drawing will now take place automatically, instead of needing an admin to do it manually.\r\n\r\nThe automated drawing still uses Random.org to determine the winner, so their randomization technique will still be used instead of doing it locally.\r\n\r\nThe drawing will occur at midnight (Audition time) on the Friday after the last Sunday of the month.\r\n\r\nIn addition, the VIP Drawing page has been re-organized a little bit and now includes a countdown until the next drawing.', 1432603084),
(218, 'Site Event', 'May VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congratulations to <a href="/community/profile/3063/">Kaisho</a> for winning the May VIP Drawing!', 1433476805),
(219, 'Site News', 'Quest Screenshots from Steam', '', 'Screenshots taken by pressing the Print Screen button in Audition on Steam are saved to "Program Files/Steam/steamapps/common/Audition Online/SCREENSHOT" by default.\r\n\r\nChange the beginning of the location to wherever you have Steam installed.', 1433647609),
(220, 'Site News', 'Recent Issues', '', 'We''ve noticed sporadic outages affecting some people over the past week.  We''re working with our hosting provider to try to fix these issues.\r\n\r\nAs of right now, everything seems to be back to normal again, but if you are still having problems, please contact us!  You can contact us through the form on the website, with a message on Facebook, or by leaving a comment on <a href="/community/profile/1/">tr848''s profile</a>.\r\n\r\nThank you so much for your patience.', 1434313800),
(221, 'Site Event', 'June VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congratulations to <a href="/community/profile/3147/">Aun</a> for winning the June VIP Drawing!', 1435896003),
(222, 'Site Update', 'Garden Timer Volume Options', '', 'Volume options have been added for the garden timer''s sound notifications.\r\n\r\nYou may have to log out and log back in to use them.', 1436408738),
(223, 'Site Update', 'Badge Bug Fixed', '', 'After winning a badge voucher from the Happy Box, if you redeem a badge that you already have, the time will now be extended instead of adding a duplicate badge with a separate expiration date.\r\n\r\nIf you ever see a bug or even something that just doesn''t look right, please do not hesitate to report it to us!  We''ll starting fixing it right away!', 1438025694),
(224, 'Site Event', 'July VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congratulations to <a href="/community/profile/1941/">Waiwai</a> for winning the July VIP Drawing!', 1438315203),
(225, 'Site Event', 'August VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congratulations to <a href="/community/profile/4013/">Veil</a> for winning the August VIP Drawing!', 1441339203),
(226, 'Site Update', 'Audifan 3.0 Alpha Testing', '', 'Alpha testing has begun for the new version of Audifan!\r\n\r\nCheck out the new site now at <a href="http://beta.audifan.net/" target="_blank">http://beta.audifan.net</a>!', 1441944976),
(229, 'Site News', 'Server Upgrade This Week', '', 'Our hosting provider will be moving Audifan to a new server sometime this week between 8pm and 2am EDT. If you are having issues connecting to the site during those hours, please try again after a few minutes. Sorry for the inconvenience.', 1443479989),
(230, 'Site News', 'ImageShack Outage', '', 'ImageShack is currently down in many areas.  New quest submissions will be hosted with Audifan while they fix the issues, but you may have trouble viewing your past submissions.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href="https://twitter.com/ImageShack/status/648856178273837056" target="_blank">https://twitter.com/ImageShack/status/648856178273837056</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\nEdit: As of October 1 at 5:00pm, ImageShack is still down. We will be making changes so that all future quest submissions will be hosted on Audifan instead of ImageShack.', 1443571113),
(231, 'Site Event', 'September VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congratulations to <a href="/community/profile/3790/">Lexia</a> for winning the September VIP Drawing!', 1443758403),
(232, 'Site Update', 'Audifan 3.0 Update Details', '', 'Complete List of Changes\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>General\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>New design and color scheme.  Every single page on Audifan has been redesigned to conform to the same template.</li>\r\n		<li>The backend of the website has been completely redesigned to be more secure and faster.</li>\r\n		<li>The menu is now mobile compatible.  Tap the button on the left to keep the menu open.  Tap it again to close it.</li>\r\n		<li>Many new links have been added to the menu for faster site navigation.</li>\r\n		<li>A "Jump to Top" link has been added to every page if you scroll down far enough.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n	\r\n	<li>New Ticket System and Help Guides\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>A new Ticket system has been added.  If you have an account issue or if you need to contact us, click the "Contact Us" link at the bottom of any page.</li>\r\n		<li>Also, guides on how to use various features of Audifan have been added to the new <a href="/help/">Help Center</a>.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Account System\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>You should now be able to log in to your account in multiple places without the sessions affecting each other.</li>\r\n		<li>The Log In and Registration pages have been integrated.</li>\r\n		<li>The new (less annoying) Recaptcha has been installed on the Registration page.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Notification System\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>The notification system has been redesigned.</li>\r\n		<li>Notifications will persist for the duration of your session instead of only appearing on one page before being deleted.</li>\r\n		<li>You can view your notifications on the homepage as well as from the top of any page with the new Notifications tab.</li>\r\n		<li>You will now receive persistent notifications for various actions that may occur while you are not logged in. These actions include:<ul>\r\n			<li>When you receive a friend request.</li>\r\n			<li>When you receive a profile comment.</li>\r\n			<li>When your quest points are updated at the end of the week.</li>\r\n			<li>When a quest submission is accepted or rejected by a grader.</li>\r\n			<li>(More will be added in the future.)</li>\r\n		</ul></li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Userbar\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>The set of links at the top of each page has been remade into a single strip instead of separate extensions.</li>\r\n		<li>VIP Status information is now at the top of every page.</li>\r\n		<li>Time until your next Happy Box spin is now at the top of every page.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Profiles\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Profiles have received a major upgrade.</li>\r\n		<li>Profile editing is now integrated into your actual profile.  Go on your profile and click the "Enter Edit Mode" button at the top.</li>\r\n		<li>While in edit mode, you can do the following:\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>Move a module around by clicking one of the Move links at the bottom of it, or click the Hide link to hide it. All of your hidden modules are at the bottom.</li>\r\n			<li>Click the Change Picture or Delete Picture links under your profile picture to change or delete it.</li>\r\n			<li>At the bottom of the Latest Comments module, you can enable or disable comments for your profile.</li>\r\n			<li>You can delete multiple favorite songs at once on the Favorite Songs module.</li>\r\n			<li>You can edit your "About Me" from within the About Me module.</li>\r\n		</ul></li>\r\n		<li>Your characters are now also listed on a separate page called "My Characters."  To edit your characters, go to the My Characters page and click the Edit link at the top.</li>\r\n		<li>When you move modules around, they will be saved immediately.  If you edit a module''s contents, it must be saved individually.</li>\r\n		<li>If you have Invisible Mode turned on, your profile will now say you''re "Offline" instead of having a separate status of "Invisible."</li>\r\n		<li>While offline, your profile will not longer display when you were last online.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Profile Comments\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Profile comments have been slightly redesigned as well.</li>\r\n		<li>Posting a comment on someone''s profile will now post it to your conversation page (previously called "Comment History") with that person.  This is to prevent confusion where you could sometimes reply to a comment by posting on your own profile (and the other person would never see it).</li>\r\n		<li>Comments posted on your own profile are now called Status Updates.</li>\r\n		<li>You can now click on the timestamp under a comment to go to that comment''s page (for easier linking).  You can delete the comment on this page as well.</li>\r\n		<li>Peach emotes have been readded.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>My Account Page\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>You will no longer be logged out after changing your password.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>My Stuff\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>You can now hide or show multiple badges at once.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Homepage\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>My Feed will now show ALL profile comments written by or recieved by your friends instead of just ones that involve you.</li>\r\n		<li>My Notifications has been added to show all notifications you have received this session. You can also delete certain notifications here.</li>\r\n		<li>The Facebook plugin is now more compact.</li>\r\n		<li>Fixed a bug where some people weren''t showing up on the VIP list.</li>\r\n		<li>Fixed a bug where if you changed your name while you were a VIP or while you have a candle, your name wouldn''t change on the homepage in the respective list.</li>\r\n		<li>Added a skip button for the image scroller.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>VIP Drawing Page\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>The form where you enter your IGN and the table of chances of winning have been separated.</li>\r\n		<li>A message to clarify that your entries will not be deleted when you remove your name from the drawing has been added.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Quests\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Quest screenshots are no longer uploaded to ImageShack.  They are now stored on Audifan.net.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Quest Homepage\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>The list of aces has been replaced with a list of ALL medalists from the previous week.</li>\r\n		<li>The Top Overall now shows the top 10 instead of top 5.  It also now shows their total QP.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Quest Rankings\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>The rankings are now paginated.</li>\r\n		<li>Fixed a bug where the rank numbers were severely messed up toward the bottom of the ranking board.</li>\r\n		<li>Fixed a bug where the rankings would skip some people.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Couple Garden Timers<ul>\r\n		<li>The Fertilize timer now correctly goes to the next 20 minute interval instead of the next 10 minute interval.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Happy Box\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Expiration times are now displayed underneath each cooldown bonus.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Member Lists\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>The list by character IGNs now shows the owner along with the character name.\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Story Guide\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>All stories for each episode are now on the same page.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Couple Shop Guide\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>The list of rings is now up-to-date.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Couple Garden Guide\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Accessory sizes have been added.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Song Lists\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Song lengths have been added to the Beat Up, Block Beat, Night Dance, Rhythmholic, and Space Pang Pang song lists.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n</ul>', 1443791398),
(233, 'Site News', 'VIP Drawing Bug (Fixed)', '', 'There is currently a bug where the first time you earn VIP Status, you will receive a glitched VIP Drawing entry that immediately expires.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe are working on fixing it right now!  We''ll edit this post when it is fixed.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEdit: The bug has been fixed and expired entries have been re-added to your account.', 1443946470),
(234, 'Site Update', '10/8 Bug Fixes', '', '- Fixed a page crash that could happen when viewing the quest homepage when you''ve never done quests before.<br />\r\n- Fixed a page crash that could happen when saving all characters on the My Characters page.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you find any bugs, please send in a ticket by clicking "Contact Us" at the bottom of any page.  Thanks!', 1444311404),
(235, 'Site Update', 'New Dark Theme', '', 'A new Dark theme has been added, which uses the same color scheme as the previous version of the site.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSwitch between the default and dark theme at the bottom of any page.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://i.imgur.com/MsTEyzV.png" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf anything on the dark theme is miscolored, please let us know!', 1444395451),
(236, 'Site Update', '10/15 Updates & Bug Fixes', '', 'Updates:<br />\r\n- Added the 10/14 patch info.<br />\r\n- Added the manual patch for versions 10301 to 10303.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBug Fixes:<br />\r\n- Fixed broken links to quest archives.<br />\r\n- If you do not list a couple with a character, that character will no longer appear with a blank couple name in My Couples on your profile.  My Teams has been changed similarly.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDark Theme Bug Fixes:<br />\r\n- Fixed background color of the Happy Box while it is loading.<br />\r\n- Fixed background color of item tooltips on the Happy Box page.<br />\r\n- Fixed background color of profile picture file selector and profile picture requirements popup.<br />\r\n- Fixed background color of character icons on profiles and on My Characters while they are loading.', 1444937081),
(237, 'Site Update', '10/22 Updates & Bug Fixes', '', 'Updates:</br>\r\n- Updated the <a href="/music/list/">song lists</a>.<br />\r\n- Added a complete list of emotes to the <a href="/help/commentsyntax/">comment syntax help guide</a>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBug Fixes:<br />\r\n- Fixed the rank numbers on the "Overall Ranking Without Insane" quest ranking board.', 1445569021),
(238, 'Site Update', 'New Time Box Guide', '/guides/timebox/', '', 1445718057),
(239, 'Site Update', 'Rhythmholic Note Counts Added', '', 'The number of notes in each Rhythmholic song as well as the number of notes per second have been added to the Rhythmholic song list.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href="/music/list/rhythmholic/">www.audifan.net/music/list/rhythmholic/</a>', 1445718139),
(240, 'Site Event', 'October VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congratulations to <a href="/community/profile/822/">Mix</a> for winning the October VIP Drawing!', 1446177604),
(241, 'Site Update', 'Recent Updates & Fixes', '', '<b>Updates:</b><br />\r\n- Added the <a href="/patch/20151111/">11/11 Patch Info</a><br />\r\n- Added a <a href="/patch/manualpatches/">manual patch</a> for version 10306<br />\r\n- Updated the <a href="/music/list/">song lists</a><br />\r\n- Updated the <a href="/community/vipdrawing/">VIP Drawing</a> winner list<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b>Bug Fixes:</b><br />\r\n- Fixed HTML appearing as regular text on the <a href="/guides/licenses/">License Guide</a><br />\r\n- Your submission status under a quest listing will now update when a new week starts without needing to log out and back in.<br />\r\n- Fixed a bug related to quest screenshot submissions.<br />\r\n- Fixed a crash that would occur after accepting a friend request for the first time.  If you were having this issue, your friend list and "My Feed" on the homepage should now be fixed.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThank you to everyone who has reported bugs!!<br />\r\nIf you find a bug, please do not hesitate to let us know. We''ll start fixing it right away!', 1447879071),
(244, 'Site Event', 'November VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congratulations to <a href="/community/profile/4205/">kevin_seidi</a> for winning the November VIP Drawing!', 1449205205),
(245, 'Site Update', '12/4 & 12/5 Updates & Fixes', '', '<b>12/4</b><br />\r\n- Added the 10308 manual patch.<br />\r\n- Fixed a bug where the time until the next drawing was incorrect on the day of the drawing on the VIP Drawing page.<br />\r\n- Added commas to quest points in comment badges and on the profile quest stats module.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b>12/5</b><br />\r\n- The Current Medalists and Top Ten Overall sections on the quest homepage are now visible while not logged in.<br />\r\n- Added quest archives from August to November 2015. There was an issue with ImageShack and only a few screenshots from August and September were able to be saved.<br />\r\n- Cleaned up old quest submissions from your submission history.', 1449284441),
(243, 'Site Update', 'New Manual Patches', '', 'A manual patch for the latest version (10307) and a manual patch with all updates from the client download version (10247) to the latest version have been added.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href="http://audifan.net/patch/manualpatches/">http://audifan.net/patch/manualpatches/</a>', 1448935710),
(246, 'Site News', '12/8 Site Maintenance', '', 'Audifan''s hosting provider will be doing maintenance on Tuesday, December 8 at about 7:30pm EST. The site may be periodically unavailable for about an hour.', 1449437860),
(248, 'Site Update', 'Dark theme is now the default', '', 'The Dark theme is now the default theme.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nYou can still change to the purple theme at the bottom of any page.', 1450297793),
(249, 'Site Update', 'Quest Expansion Update', '', 'New quests are here, in addition to medal changes, profile module changes, and a few fixes.  Check out all of the details below!<br />\r\n<ul><br />\r\n	<li>2 new quest types have been added.<ul><br />\r\n		<li>Group Quest - The group quest will require the help of at least one other person in order to complete it. The group quest is worth 10 points.</li><br />\r\n		<li>Battle Quest - More info is below.</li><br />\r\n		<li>The Easy, Medium, Hard, and Insane quests are now collectively called "Individual Quests" since they can be completed alone and the points you receive from them are independent of everyone else.</li><br />\r\n		</ul></li><br />\r\n	<li>About the new Battle Quest<ul><br />\r\n		<li>The battle quest offers variable quest points based on how well you met the objective compared to all others who also submitted a screenshot for it.</li><br />\r\n		<li>Examples of Battle Quest objectives are "Get as many points as you can" in a certain mode, "Get as many Perfects as you can" in Beat Up, or even "Get as many Bads as you can" in a certain mode.</li><br />\r\n		<li>When your screenshot is graded, the score, number of perfects, etc. that you got will be recorded by the grader.  The value that was recorded for the screenshot will be listed under "Status Message" on the submission details page once it has been graded so you can check it.<br><img src="http://i.imgur.com/CS3vrwe.png" style="border:1px solid #fff; border-radius:2px; padding:2px; margin:2px;" /></li><br />\r\n		<li>Once the screenshot is graded as complete, you cannot submit another screenshot (e.g. if you got a better score). The screenshot you submit should be your best and final attempt.</li><br />\r\n		<li>At the end of the week, when points are updated, you will receive at least 6 QP.  The number of QP you''ll receive increases depending on how many people participated and how well you did compared to everyone else.  The maximum number of QP you can receive from the Battle Quest is 20.</li><br />\r\n		<li>You can see the current range of points under the Battle Quest objective. The top placer will always receive the maximum number of points and the person in last place will always receive the minimum number of points. Everyone in between will receive points proportional to the score, number of perfects, etc. that they got compared to everyone else.</li><br />\r\n		<li>Once points are updated, the "Status Message" on the submission details page will update with the number of points that you received for the Battle Quest.<br /><img src="http://i.imgur.com/wkM0QWK.png" style="border:1px solid #fff; border-radius:2px; padding:2px; margin:2px;" /></li><br />\r\n		<li>A small ranking board has been added to the quest homepage that will show the ranking for the previous week''s Battle Quest and how many QP each person received.</li><br />\r\n		</ul></li><br />\r\n	<li>Individual Quest Medal Changes<ul><br />\r\n		<li>Medals are now awarded based on how many Individual Quests you complete, instead of which specific quests you complete.</li><br />\r\n		<li>For example, if you complete the Easy, Medium, and Insane quests, you will now receive the Silver Medal instead of just the Bronze medal.</li><br />\r\n		</ul></li><br />\r\n	<li>Additional Changes<ul><br />\r\n		<li>A new "Individual Quests only" ranking board has been added that excludes Group and Battle quest points.</li><br />\r\n		<li>The Quest Stats profile module has been redone and now has much more information about the quests you''ve completed and your ranks.</li><br />\r\n		<li>All ranking boards now show each person''s total QP in addition to the ranked QP amount, for easier comparison.</li><br />\r\n		<li>Ranking board descriptions have been re-added.</li><br />\r\n		<li>Some quest requirements have been adjusted down to better match their difficulty levels.</li><br />\r\n		<li>Screenshots viewed on the submission details page will now pop up on the page instead of opening in a new tab.</li><br />\r\n		<li>Fixed the "log in" link on the Submit a Screenshot page.</li><br />\r\n		<li>Fixed a bug where you could submit a screenshot for the "Spin the Happy Box" quest.</li><br />\r\n		</ul></li><br />\r\n	<li>Notes<ul><br />\r\n		<li>Mode-specific ranking boards do not include Group or Battle quest points. Only Easy, Normal, Hard, and Insane quest points are used in determining mode ranks.</li>\r\n		</ul></li>\r\n</ul><br />\r\n<br />\r\nAs always, we would love to have your feedback!  Click the Contact Us link at the bottom of any page to send in a ticket, or send tr848 a message on Redbana Forums!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThank you for using Audifan!', 1450625620),
(250, 'Site Event', 'Grab a Badge!', '', 'From now until the end of the year, you will receive a badge from the <a href="/community/happybox/">Happy Box</a> if you do not win anything else.', 1451039046),
(251, 'Site Event', 'December VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congratulations to K9 for winning the December VIP Drawing!', 1451888062),
(254, 'Site Update', 'New Coin System & Megaphones', '', 'A new coin system, Happy Box updates, a new megaphone system, and more have been added to Audifan!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSpin the Happy Box to earn coins.  Purchase badges, a Happy Box cooldown item, and megaphone tickets at the new Coin Store.  Plus, use megaphone tickets to broadcast to everyone on Audifan with the new community megaphone!  That''s the gist, but check out all of the details below!<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>New Coin System<ul>\r\n		<li>How to earn coins<ul>\r\n			<li>Spin the Happy Box<ul>\r\n				<li>If you do not win anything else from the Happy Box, you will receive between 10 and 50 coins.</li>\r\n				<li>JACKPOT!<ul>\r\n					<li>Each time someone wins coins from the Happy Box, the same amount is added to the Happy Box Jackpot.</li>\r\n					<li>Once the Jackpot reaches 1,000 coins, anyone who spins has a chance to win all of the coins in the Jackpot.  Also, after the Jackpot reaches 1,000 coins, the chance of winning the Jackpot increases by 0.01% every time more coins are added to it.</li>\r\n					<li>The current Jackpot and current chance of winning the Jackpot appear just above the Happy Box.</li>\r\n					<li>The amount of coins you earn from the Jackpot is not increased by Coin Bonuses (more info below).</li>\r\n				</ul></li>\r\n			</ul></li>\r\n			<li>Open Coin Boxes<ul>\r\n				<li>Coin Boxes can be won from the Happy Box and from future events.</li>\r\n				<li>You will also receive a Coin Box if you log in 3 days in a week and a Double Coin Box if you log in 6 days in a week.</li>\r\n				<li>There are 4 types of Coin Boxes: Regular (simply called Coin Box), Double, Triple, and Mystery<ul>\r\n					<li>The regular Coin Box contains between 200 and 400 coins.</li>\r\n					<li>The Double Coin Box contains double the amount of coins as the regular Coin Box.</li>\r\n					<li>The Triple Coin Box contains triple the amount of coins as the regular Coin Box.</li>\r\n					<li>The Mystery Coin Box will either contain a large amount of coins or a +25% Coin Bonus Item (more info below).</li>\r\n				</ul></li>\r\n				<li>You can open Coin Boxes on the <a href="/account/stuff/">My Stuff</a> page.  If you have more than one coin box, you can open all of them at once at the bottom of the "Coin Boxes" section. When you open multiple, the boxes that are closest to expiring are opened first.</li>\r\n			</ul></li>\r\n		</ul></li>\r\n		<li>How to increase the coins you earn<ul>\r\n			<li>Coin Bonus items can be won from the Happy Box.<ul>\r\n				<li>There are +5%, +15%, and +25% Bonus Items that can be won.  They increase the coins you earn from all sources by the respective amount.</li>\r\n				<li>These items expire 7 days after you win one.</li>\r\n				<li>Winning a better Coin Bonus item will replace lesser ones (e.g. a +25% Coin Bonus item will replace a +5% Coin Bonus item).</li>\r\n			</ul></li>\r\n			<li>Veteran Bonus<ul>\r\n				<li>If your account is at least one year old, the coins you receive from all sources is increased by 10%.</li>\r\n			</ul></li>\r\n		</ul></li>\r\n		<li>You can see your current coin balance, a list of all coin bonuses that are active on your account, and a history of all coin transactions on the My Stuff page.</li>\r\n		<li>Buying Stuff at the <a href="/store/">Coin Store</a><ul>\r\n			<li>Badges can be purchased for 7 days. They will appear next to your name. A badge cannot be purchased if you have any unclaimed Badge Vouchers in My Stuff.</li>\r\n			<li>A -10% Happy Box Cooldown item can be purchased, which reduces the time between Happy Box spins by 10%.  This item cannot be purchased if you already have a -40% Cooldown item.</li>\r\n			<li>Megaphone tickets can be purchased for the new community megaphone (more info below).</li>\r\n		</ul></li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n	<li>New Community Megaphone<ul>\r\n		<li>Megaphones will broadcast a message at the top of every page on Audifan.</li>\r\n		<li>Click the Megaphone link at the top of any page to see all current megaphones and to create your own.</li>\r\n		<li>You must have a megaphone ticket to use it.  They can be purchased at the Coin Store or won from the Happy Box.</li>\r\n		<li>Megaphones will last for 24 hours.</li>\r\n		<li>You may have a maximum of 3 concurrent megaphones.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n	<li>Additional Happy Box Changes<ul>\r\n		<li>The -10% Cooldown item can no longer be won from the Happy Box.  It can now be purchased at the Coin Store.</li>\r\n		<li>The -25% Cooldown item has been removed. If you currently have one, it will continue to work until it expires.</li>\r\n		<li>-40% Cooldown items won from the Happy Box now last 7 days (up from 5 days).</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n	<li>Bug Fixes<ul>\r\n		<li>Fixed a bug where quest medals, the VIP badge, and the CA badge were counted as voucher badges, which prevented the Happy Box from awarding a Badge Voucher if you had at least two of them.</li>\r\n		<li>Fixed a crash on the page that resends the verification code for a new account.</li>\r\n	</ul></li>\r\n</ul><br />\r\nIf you find any issues or have any question, please contact us by leaving tr848 a comment or by using the Contact Us link at the bottom of any page.  Thank you for using Audifan!<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b><u>Hotfixes</u></b><br />\r\n<b>2/8</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed a page crash on the My Stuff page that occurred if you tried to view it while not logged in.</li>\r\n<li>Fixed prices appearing as 0 at the Coin Store.</li>\r\n<li>Fixed the megaphone ticket tooltip on the Happy Box page.</li>\r\n</ul>', 1454952893),
(253, 'Site Event', 'January VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congratulations to <a href="/community/profile/4306/">Mage</a> for winning the January VIP Drawing!', 1454648402),
(255, 'Site Event', 'Facebook Giveaway', '', 'To celebrate the new coin and megaphone features, we''re giving away a Double Coin Box and 2 megaphone tickets to everyone who comments on this post on Audifan''s Facebook page:<br />\r\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/audifan/posts/932826620086407" target="_blank">https://www.facebook.com/audifan/posts/932826620086407</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\nEnds on February 22!', 1454955159),
(256, 'Site Update', '2/17 Updates', '', 'Added December 2015 and January 2016 quest archives.<br />\r\nRemoved old quest submissions from the submission history.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMultiple notifications for when quest submissions are accepted by a grader will now be combined into one notification.<br />\r\nBefore, you would receive up to six redundant "A quest submission was accepted" notifications, but now there will be only one notification that updates as the rest of your submissions are graded.<br />\r\nWe''ll be doing this for other types of notifications (such as multiple friend requests or profile comments) in the future.', 1455767543),
(257, 'Site Update', '2/29 Updates', '', '- Added a new "Recent Happy Box Prizes" profile module.  It is hidden by default and can be added by going to Edit Mode on your profile and adding it from the list of hidden modules at the bottom.<br />\r\n- Updated the song list.<br />\r\n- The list of current medalists on the Quest homepage is now in alphabetical order.', 1456768584),
(258, 'Site Event', 'February VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congratulations to <a href="/community/profile/4388/">Shea</a> for winning the February VIP Drawing!', 1457067605),
(259, 'Site Update', '3/5 Bug Fixes', '', '- Fixed level titles always appearing as hidden on your profile and My Characters page.<br />\r\n- Fixed the maximum level to display as "MAX" instead of "Lv. 99"<br />\r\n- Fixed some alignment issues on the My Characters page.', 1457206400),
(260, 'Site Update', '3/24 Updates and Bug Fixes', '', 'Updates:<br />\r\n- Notifications will now be deleted after 2 weeks.<br />\r\n- A new system has been added which alerts admins to new tickets in a better way.  This should improve ticket response time.<br />\r\n- Added clarification that the VIP Drawing prize will be sent to the IGN that you entered the drawing with.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBug Fixes:<br />\r\n- The VIP Drawing prize voucher is now properly set to indefinite duration after you claim it.', 1458846286),
(261, 'Site Event', 'March VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congratulations to <a href="/community/profile/4128/">JaeKae</a> for winning the March VIP Drawing!', 1459483202),
(262, 'Site Update', '4/3 Updates', '', '- Added a new "My Stuff Notices" section on the homepage.  When you have unopened coin boxes or unclaimed prize vouchers, the section will appear to let you know.<br />\r\n- Re-added the ability to expand and contract your feed on the homepage.', 1459694268),
(263, 'Site Event', 'Coin Store Sale', '', 'Everything at the <a href="/store/">Coin Store</a> is 25% off until Friday, April 8!', 1459695579),
(264, 'Site Update', '4/8 Updates', '', '- The Happy Box now uses HTML5.  You should now be able to spin it on a mobile device!<br />\r\n- The Happy Box now shows how many hours your cooldown has been reduced.<br />\r\n- Added relative drop rates to the list of prizes on the Happy Box page.<br />\r\n- Entries in "My Coin History" on the My Stuff page will now be deleted after 30 days.', 1460132121),
(265, 'Site Update', '4/14 - 4/16 Updates/Bug Fix', '', 'Updates:<br />\r\n- Added new patch info.<br />\r\n- Updated the song list.<br />\r\n- Added the latest manual patch.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBug Fix:<br />\r\n- Fixed the Candle Day badge image in My Stuff.', 1460813621),
(266, 'Site Event', 'April VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congratulations to <a href="/community/profile/1224/">Meerkat</a> for winning the April VIP Drawing!', 1461902405),
(267, 'Site Update', '5/20 Updates', '', '- Added a Guitar Tournament Badge.  It can be purchased at the Coin Store or redeemed from a Badge Voucher won from the Happy Box.<br />\r\n- Updated the tooltip on badges to say that they can also be purchased at the Coin Store.', 1463794016),
(268, 'Site Event', 'May VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congratulations to <a href="/community/profile/4368/">Minaa</a> for winning the May VIP Drawing!', 1464926404),
(269, 'Site Update', '6/4 Updates', '', 'Added profile picture thumbnails in these places:<br />\r\n- My Feed<br />\r\n- Latest Comments module on profiles<br />\r\n- Comment pages<br />\r\n- Conversation pages<br />\r\n- Happy Box recent winners.', 1465064491),
(270, 'Site Event', 'June VIP Drawing Winner', '', 'Congratulations to <a href="/community/profile/3694/">Svm</a> for winning the June VIP Drawing!', 1467345602),
(271, 'Site Update', '7/3 Updates', '', 'Profile comments and feed posts now only show your badges under your name.  To see more info (VIP ranking, quest info, etc.) click the arrow.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nYour main character''s info is also now included in the extended section.  To change your main character, go to My Characters, click Edit Characters, and scroll all the way to the bottom.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf something doesn''t look right, press Ctrl+F5 to do a hard refresh.', 1467565457),
